1. Install Kaldi on your macine. 
   Follow the instruction here http://kaldi.sourceforge.net/tutorial_setup.html

2. Get voxforge data from Yiping and put them into deep-ipa/asr/voxforge_data

3. Apply patch by running kaldi_patch.sh. Change the kaldi root dir in the script first.
   (You do need to run ./deploy.sh in socket-lib and change the kaldi root there also)

4. And the above script will also copy multiple data and graph dir to your kaldi directory
   It copies over the following things
   1) raw mfcc data -> voxforge/s5/data_set/mfcc
   2) target data set (deepblue_set) -> voxforge/s5/data/deepblue_test
   3) graph dir -> voxforge/s5/exp/tri3b
   4) decode config file -> voxforge/s5/conf/decode_dnn.config
   5) Feature transfomration network and local dnn -> voxforge/s5/exp/dnn5b_pretrain-dbn_dnn/
   6)* It change the directory pointer sed -i 's~/home/ypkang/kaldi-trunk/~NEW_KALDI_ROOT~g' file

5. Navigate to src/nnetbin and type make to recompile nnet-forward binary

6. Navigate to kaldi_root/egs/voxforge/s5 and run_client.sh like the following
  ./run_client.sh <server-addr> <portno> <use-service?> <debug>
  e.g. ./run_client.sh localhost 8080 true 1
